post_text:
Happy Friday!

I'm happy to announce we have all made it through our first week of school! There have been lots of changes and protocols to remember, but everyone has stayed positive and in high sprits. If you have any questions please feel welcome to email me at kgoulet@westbathschool.org.

Enjoy your weekend & see you Monday! üçç

post_text: Almost all of you were able to pick up your remote learning packets today and I was glad to see a few friendly faces! Our remote learning lessons don't officially start until Monday 3/23. I am still waiting on login information for IXL and Read Theory, so when I have it I will send it out. In the meantime you can play math games online, independently read (I tried to find everyone a few books) or try some of the links I've included. This is a new experience for all of us- stay positive and keep checking in! :)

post_text: It has been a busy day for 5th Grade! We began at the Gulf of Maine Research Institute and learned about different species that live in the gulf. We collected data and used it to support our claims. Then, we walked the streets of Portland to interview people about their knowledge of human rights and gave out informational bookmarks. Winter concert tonight! See you at 5:15!

We will be holding our concert outside this evening at 5:30, as the weather is dry and the field is manageable. Avoid wearing heals, knowing that you will come across some soggy spots. Parking will be at the courthouse with shuttle service to the school beginning at 5 PM. Students should join their class seating area upon arrival, with the exception of band students who should meet in the library at 5:15. We will have chairs set up for those who need one, otherwise feel free to bring your own or a blanket to spread out on. Please note that the playground will be closed before and during the concert, but available afterwards! We look forward to seeing everyone this evening!

post_text:
BOSTON INFORMATION!

Only two days until we journey to Boston!

Please be at the Brunswick Train Station by 7:15am. Pick up is at 8:00pm (we will keep the FB page updated if there are any delays).

Please make sure your child has the following:
-Comfortable sneakers
-Backpack
-Bag lunch (no glass containers) if not ordered through school
-Water bottle filled w/ water
-Snacks for the morning train ride
-Jacket

For dinner we will be using fundraising money to order pizzas. We will eat on the train ride home. Extra money can be brought to buy an additional snack on the train.

Thank you!

shared_text:
West Bath School
May 4, 2018 at 2:45 PM ¬∑

What an amazing #BetterWorldDay!! Our K-2 students raked, weeded, mulched, and planted our gardens to beautify our spaces and support our pollinators. Grade 3 students raked and cleaned the cemetery at Birch Point to support the West Bath Cemetery Committee. Grade 4 worked with Kennebec Estuary Land Trust to collect data on the vernal pools at Green Point Preserve. Grade 5 also worked at Green Point Preserve to trim trees, clear trails, and carry lumber for bridge building. It was a wonderful day of service, and we are so pleased to be able to give back to our community. Many more pictures to come!! #WeAreCrew #BetterWorldDay #WBSCares
